00:00:50.460 --> 00:00:51.910
"Hello, Antonio!

00:00:51.910 --> 00:00:55.890
I'm a 26-year-old man living in Los Angeles.

00:00:55.890 --> 00:01:00.579
Not too long ago, I was wearing jeans, shirts,
rubber shoes, and I didn’t really put too

00:01:00.579 --> 00:01:02.160
much emphasis on my style.

00:01:02.160 --> 00:01:04.739
I dressed shabbily and I never noticed.

00:01:04.739 --> 00:01:08.710
Trucker hats were a staple of my wardrobe
because I found it easier to rush out the

00:01:08.710 --> 00:01:11.330
door and cover my hair than to style it.

00:01:11.330 --> 00:01:14.390
One day, my girlfriend told me she wanted
to get out of our relationship.

00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:17.750
She mentioned that my dress was one of the
factors in her decision.

00:01:17.750 --> 00:01:20.290
I realized that my father had been right.

00:01:20.290 --> 00:01:22.360
Be a man and dress nice."

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:27.140
"I always had the clothes in my drawers and
closets, so why not figure out how to put

00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.960
everything together and get my sizes right?

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:33.290
I dug into your website, watched your videos,
read your articles.

00:01:33.290 --> 00:01:37.970
I even picked up a copy of 'Dressing the Man'
by Alan Flusser and tore into it late in the

00:01:37.970 --> 00:01:41.479
night, which has surprised everyone because
I hardly ever read.

00:01:41.479 --> 00:01:43.130
I didn’t even have to pay for it.

00:01:43.130 --> 00:01:47.380
My local library had it, so I've been studying
for the last few weeks.

00:01:47.380 --> 00:01:50.770
Thank you for the review; it is a great book."

00:01:50.770 --> 00:01:55.560
"Now, I haven't got much financially, so at
first, I really didn’t know about how to

00:01:55.560 --> 00:02:00.830
go getting a wardrobe together, but in one
of your videos, you mentioned thrift stores.

00:02:00.830 --> 00:02:04.770
And so, although I had always gone to these
with my parents as a youngster, but suddenly

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:08.830
stopped going, I decided to jump in and to
see what was out there.

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:14.709
To my surprise, I now have a wonderful suit,
no alterations necessary, a few Brooks Brothers

00:02:14.709 --> 00:02:19.540
shirts, and I recently came into possession
of a Thomas Pink shirt.

00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:22.540
Quality over quantity is something you've
now imprinted in my mind.

00:02:22.540 --> 00:02:27.440
I've been hemming my jeans and trousers, a
skill I picked up from my mother, and making

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:30.209
sure all of my clothes fit me properly."

00:02:30.209 --> 00:02:34.550
"My mom is excited to see how I'm dressing
now.

00:02:34.550 --> 00:02:38.680
Every time I come by the house, my father
keeps digging through his own wardrobe to

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:43.040
see if there's anything that I can fit and
that I can use.

00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:45.460
He also gave me some great shoes.

00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:50.450
The short time I've been dressing properly
has made a huge impact on how others view

00:02:50.450 --> 00:02:53.570
me, both in my personal life and my work.

00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:57.530
You're right when you say that dressing nice
does boost self-esteem.

00:02:57.530 --> 00:03:03.560
I went to a wedding a few days ago and everyone
was complimenting me on my attire.

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:09.150
I walked into the reception and everyone looked
at me, and the night included numerous questions

00:03:09.150 --> 00:03:12.940
as to how I created this wardrobe.

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:15.160
All I told them to do was check out your website."

00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:20.580
"I've even inspired my best friend to go shopping
with me and find his own wardrobe, and my

00:03:20.580 --> 00:03:25.239
father is now also looking through his closet
to wear his very best.

00:03:25.239 --> 00:03:30.489
I thank you for starting me on this journey
and I know it will last a lifetime.

00:03:30.489 --> 00:03:31.690
Juan."

00:03:31.690 --> 00:03:34.090
All right.

00:03:34.090 --> 00:03:37.030
I really like that story, again, for two reasons.

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:41.980
One is you heard Juan doesn’t have a whole
lot of money, but yet he was able to take

00:03:41.980 --> 00:03:42.980
the skills.

00:03:42.980 --> 00:03:43.980
He built an education.

00:03:43.980 --> 00:03:47.450
He went to his local library and found some
of the books I've suggested.

00:03:47.450 --> 00:03:50.910
He went through my website, checked out all
these videos that's all for free.

00:03:50.910 --> 00:03:53.790
First, he invested in himself.

00:03:53.790 --> 00:03:58.239
