00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.239
He knew what to look for.

00:04:00.239 --> 00:04:02.810
He found a suit that didn’t even need alterations.

00:04:02.810 --> 00:04:08.170
He was able to identify quality shirts and
he started piecing his wardrobe together.

00:04:08.170 --> 00:04:13.569
And really quick, it sounds like he didn’t
go to a seamstress or a tailor.

00:04:13.569 --> 00:04:18.670
He actually started sewing some of his own
clothing, which a lot of people think it's

00:04:18.670 --> 00:04:21.470
almost impossible, but it's really not that
difficult.

00:04:21.470 --> 00:04:25.630
So if you're out there and you don't have
a whole lot of money, that is always an option.

00:04:25.630 --> 00:04:27.740
Just buy something cheap and practice on it.

00:04:27.740 --> 00:04:33.680
The other thing I think that Juan is really
learning is that every journey of a thousand

00:04:33.680 --> 00:04:36.690
miles begins with a single step.

00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:40.020
And so, he is building up his self-confidence
at home.

00:04:40.020 --> 00:04:43.220
It's helping him with his relationships with
others.

00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:47.970
And when you can do this, when you start to
feel this self-confidence, all of a sudden,

00:04:47.970 --> 00:04:49.440
